    {
      "id": "cd68a4a64d11ff159fdfaa4de39268f5ac11f6de",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2019-08-13 22:31:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis is more complex than that. I have had issues with the native lustre client. I see RCU issues. Haven't had cycles to fix this yet.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "9eb261b838cd68fa8fa9578defae1101d3e64e6b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2019-08-13 22:51:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHmm ... if you are seeing RCU issues then it's probably best to refactor this from rntl to rcu ... and get rid of the realloc() loop in the process.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e3a337c8abb6b386533e7821a594e9bd56f02b43",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2019-08-26 13:33:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nI was going off what was happening upstream. This weekend I tracked down the rcu issues and found it to be the use of in_dev_for_each_ifa_rcu() which expect rcu_read_lock() / rcu_read_unlock() to be called. You used the correct function in_dev_for_each_ifa_rtnl(). I do still o2iblnd problems but its due to other issues I haven't figured out yet.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
